WEBVTT

1
00:03:21.609 --> 00:03:23.541
The heart...

2
00:03:31.509 --> 00:03:32.941
...for Smoke Frog.

3
00:03:33.009 --> 00:03:34.270
Thank you.

4
00:03:40.409 --> 00:03:42.466
This liver for Curl Nose.

5
00:03:42.809 --> 00:03:44.536
Thank you.

6
00:03:49.343 --> 00:03:50.603
Cocoa Leaf...

7
00:03:50.776 --> 00:03:51.935
...the ears.

8
00:03:52.076 --> 00:03:53.372
Thank you.

9
00:03:56.243 --> 00:03:57.799
And for you Blunted...

10
00:04:00.610 --> 00:04:02.200
...the balls.

11
00:04:05.510 --> 00:04:06.635
Not this again.

12
00:04:07.076 --> 00:04:08.064
I'm helping you.

13
00:04:08.276 --> 00:04:09.401
Then you eat them!

14
00:04:09.576 --> 00:04:11.905
I don't need them.
Neither do the rest of the fellows.

15
00:04:12.009 --> 00:04:13.032
Do you fellows?

16
00:04:13.109 --> 00:04:13.871
No.

17
00:04:13.942 --> 00:04:14.909
Of course not!

18
00:04:14.976 --> 00:04:16.237
Sometimes!

19
00:04:16.476 --> 00:04:17.271
What do you think?

20
00:04:17.643 --> 00:04:18.438
No!

21
00:04:18.510 --> 00:04:19.407
No. no!

22
00:04:20.010 --> 00:04:21.771
But how many times does it take?

23
00:04:22.010 --> 00:04:24.635
I have eight older sisters
and one brother.

24
00:04:24.977 --> 00:04:28.374
Father took tapir balls all ten times.

25
00:05:08.910 --> 00:05:10.274
Shall I tell him?

26
00:05:12.310 --> 00:05:14.606
I'm sorry. The balls are useless.

27
00:05:16.844 --> 00:05:18.036
You've never had them?

28
00:05:18.344 --> 00:05:20.810
Couldn't tell you what they taste like.

29
00:05:21.811 --> 00:05:22.902
None of you?

30
00:05:24.911 --> 00:05:27.570
No. but it's been fun watching you...

31
00:05:33.411 --> 00:05:34.434
This was your idea!

32
00:05:37.411 --> 00:05:38.707
Get him off me!

33
00:05:45.577 --> 00:05:47.203
Calm down!

34
00:06:04.645 --> 00:06:07.611
Why do you let them treat you like this?

35
00:06:08.145 --> 00:06:09.634
Be strong.

36
00:06:10.311 --> 00:06:11.709
Where is your pride?

37
00:06:16.745 --> 00:06:19.802
It all works... Yes?

38
00:06:23.245 --> 00:06:24.438
Yes...

39
00:06:24.978 --> 00:06:27.740
...I just can't make children.

40
00:06:33.178 --> 00:06:35.736
There is something I will tell you...

41
00:06:36.445 --> 00:06:39.707
...but I warn you. it's very powerful.

42
00:06:41.345 --> 00:06:42.141
What do you speak of?

43
00:06:42.945 --> 00:06:44.535
The soanzo leaf.

44
00:06:45.945 --> 00:06:47.309
The soanzo leaf?

45
00:06:47.578 --> 00:06:50.238
From the great marshes in the south...

46
00:06:55.079 --> 00:06:58.102
This is what gave me my ten children.

47
00:07:04.446 --> 00:07:06.638
No! No! Wait...

48
00:07:07.979 --> 00:07:10.309
You have to rub them on... down there.

49
00:07:11.012 --> 00:07:13.274
Just before you next try.

50
00:07:13.513 --> 00:07:15.570
Apply it generously...

51
00:07:20.179 --> 00:07:22.236
I don't know how to thank you.

52
00:07:24.246 --> 00:07:27.406
If this works...
maybe she'll stop bothering me.

53
00:07:27.846 --> 00:07:28.937
Your wife?

54
00:07:29.413 --> 00:07:31.242
No. her mother.

55
00:07:31.579 --> 00:07:33.977
The old hag wants grandchildren.

56
00:07:43.513 --> 00:07:45.070
Give me some meat.

57
00:07:45.579 --> 00:07:47.568
Here. work on this...

58
00:07:47.980 --> 00:07:49.809
...pure meat...

59
00:07:51.479 --> 00:07:53.809
...ball breath.

60
00:08:58.181 --> 00:08:59.306
What do you want?

61
00:09:03.747 --> 00:09:05.043
What do you want?

62
00:10:00.481 --> 00:10:05.641
I am Flint Sky. I have hunted
this forest from the day I came of age.

63
00:10:07.149 --> 00:10:11.547
My father hunted this forest
with me and before me.

64
00:10:13.182 --> 00:10:15.114
Jaguar Paw. my son.

65
00:10:15.416 --> 00:10:17.745
He hunts this forest with me.

66
00:10:19.282 --> 00:10:22.770
He will hunt it with his son
after I am gone.

67
00:10:42.916 --> 00:10:44.279
A good catch?

68
00:10:45.115 --> 00:10:47.081
Good waters here.

69
00:10:49.749 --> 00:10:51.214
The forest gives much here.

70
00:10:57.315 --> 00:10:59.247
We ask only to pass through.

71
00:11:00.116 --> 00:11:01.411
Pass.

72
00:11:07.283 --> 00:11:09.112
Keep safe as you pass.

73
00:11:12.749 --> 00:11:14.306
Let's go.

74
00:11:51.083 --> 00:11:53.242
Our lands were ravaged.

75
00:11:54.116 --> 00:11:56.049
We seek a new beginning.

76
00:12:03.017 --> 00:12:04.573
Your lands were ravaged?

77
00:12:08.316 --> 00:12:09.942
Yes...

78
00:12:11.251 --> 00:12:13.944
We seek a new beginning...

79
00:12:14.517 --> 00:12:15.778
Be still.

80
00:12:16.017 --> 00:12:16.948
My son!

81
00:12:18.950 --> 00:12:20.211
Be still.

82
00:12:25.351 --> 00:12:26.646
Back to the village.

83
00:13:00.351 --> 00:13:05.249
I ask you not to speak
of what you saw in the forest today.

84
00:13:09.152 --> 00:13:11.277
You are troubled.

85
00:13:11.518 --> 00:13:13.246
Yes. I am.

86
00:13:29.751 --> 00:13:33.877
Those people in the forest.
what did you see on them?

87
00:13:34.419 --> 00:13:35.578
I do not understand.

88
00:13:36.684 --> 00:13:38.150
Fear.

89
00:13:41.452 --> 00:13:44.418
Deep rotting fear.

90
00:13:44.985 --> 00:13:47.543
They were infected by it.

91
00:13:48.419 --> 00:13:49.715
Did you see?

92
00:13:50.252 --> 00:13:52.411
Fear is a sickness.

93
00:13:57.685 --> 00:14:01.811
It will crawl into the soul
of anyone who engages it.

94
00:14:03.619 --> 00:14:07.779
It has tainted your peace already.

95
00:14:09.986 --> 00:14:14.078
I did not raise you
to see you live with fear.

96
00:14:16.619 --> 00:14:18.313
Strike it from your heart.

97
00:14:18.519 --> 00:14:21.213
Do not bring it into our village.

98
00:14:21.752 --> 00:14:25.378
At first light
we will gather with the elders...

99
00:14:26.286 --> 00:14:29.411
...at the sacred hill of our fathers.

100
00:14:30.186 --> 00:14:34.448
There we will call on
their spirits to guide us.

101
00:14:45.620 --> 00:14:47.313
Oh. here he is!

102
00:14:48.286 --> 00:14:49.616
The big lump!

103
00:14:50.453 --> 00:14:51.918
He's useless.

104
00:14:52.620 --> 00:14:54.108
He can't do it.

105
00:14:55.919 --> 00:14:57.408
You! Yes you!

106
00:14:58.153 --> 00:15:01.551
With your height and your girth.
You have deceived us.

107
00:15:02.620 --> 00:15:03.881
Get inside!

108
00:15:09.420 --> 00:15:10.943
Damn you! Get in there!

109
00:15:11.286 --> 00:15:12.775
Old woman. please.

110
00:15:13.186 --> 00:15:14.153
Move it!

111
00:15:18.520 --> 00:15:19.986
You don't work!

112
00:15:22.520 --> 00:15:23.986
What are you laughing about?

113
00:15:31.953 --> 00:15:36.443
Give me a grandchild
or I will have you replaced.

114
00:15:37.620 --> 00:15:39.484
Mother. that's enough.

115
00:15:40.487 --> 00:15:43.578
Do not come out until you make a child.

116
00:15:45.254 --> 00:15:46.776
Two would be better!

117
00:15:47.020 --> 00:15:47.951
What?

118
00:15:49.621 --> 00:15:51.610
Twins you oaf.

119
00:16:00.354 --> 00:16:01.115
Mother.

120
00:16:02.087 --> 00:16:06.417
Can you go away?
He says he can't with you sitting there.

121
00:16:06.854 --> 00:16:08.217
Just get busy.

122
00:16:09.487 --> 00:16:10.783
Mom...

123
00:16:15.421 --> 00:16:16.887
She's gone.

124
00:17:00.422 --> 00:17:03.149
Mother. what do you say we should
have at the feast tonight?

125
00:17:03.422 --> 00:17:06.115
I have tapir...
but I also found this boy.

126
00:17:06.822 --> 00:17:07.549
I say boy.

127
00:17:07.755 --> 00:17:08.652
Roasted!

128
00:17:08.922 --> 00:17:11.547
The tapir smells better.
I think it's more fresh.

129
00:17:11.955 --> 00:17:13.887
No Dad! No! It's me! It's me!

130
00:17:14.088 --> 00:17:16.884
I'll just hang the boy here
in case we change our minds.

131
00:17:20.455 --> 00:17:21.149
Wait...

132
00:17:21.355 --> 00:17:24.220
That's our Turtles Run.
That's our eldest.

133
00:17:24.422 --> 00:17:26.888
Yes it's me. It's your eldest!

134
00:17:27.789 --> 00:17:31.085
In that case. a crush for my eldest...

135
00:17:34.688 --> 00:17:36.984
...and a crush for my youngest.

136
00:17:38.256 --> 00:17:40.585
Tapir it is.

137
00:18:46.623 --> 00:18:48.055
One day. old man!

138
00:18:48.623 --> 00:18:50.919
One day you won't be able
to run anymore!

139
00:19:08.624 --> 00:19:11.749
And a Man sat alone.

140
00:19:13.190 --> 00:19:15.713
Drenched deep in sadness.

141
00:19:16.424 --> 00:19:19.219
And all the animals
drew near to him and said:

142
00:19:19.857 --> 00:19:23.653
"We do not like to see you so sad...

143
00:19:25.457 --> 00:19:28.890
"Ask us for whatever you wish
and you shall have it."

144
00:19:29.924 --> 00:19:34.288
The Man said:
"I want to have good sight."

145
00:19:35.690 --> 00:19:38.884
The vulture replied:
"You shall have mine."

146
00:19:41.924 --> 00:19:45.118
The Man said: "I want to be strong."

147
00:19:48.824 --> 00:19:50.585
The jaguar said:

148
00:19:52.957 --> 00:19:55.889
"You shall be strong like me."

149
00:19:57.857 --> 00:20:03.721
Then the Man said: "I long
to know the secrets of the earth."

150
00:20:05.291 --> 00:20:10.246
The serpent replied:
"I will show them to you."

151
00:20:12.158 --> 00:20:14.647
And so it went with all the animals.

152
00:20:16.358 --> 00:20:19.085
And when the Man had
all the gifts that they could give...

153
00:20:19.291 --> 00:20:20.917
...he left.

154
00:20:22.491 --> 00:20:24.753
Then the owl said to the other animals:

155
00:20:25.691 --> 00:20:29.555
"Now the Man knows much
and is able to do many things...

156
00:20:30.658 --> 00:20:33.988
"Suddenly I am afraid."

157
00:20:37.192 --> 00:20:39.987
The deer said:
"The Man has all that he needs."

158
00:20:41.125 --> 00:20:43.114
"Now his sadness will stop."

159
00:20:43.758 --> 00:20:45.747
But the owl replied: "No."

160
00:20:48.425 --> 00:20:51.290
"I saw a hole in the Man...

161
00:20:52.292 --> 00:20:56.054
"Deep like a hunger
he will never fill...

162
00:20:57.092 --> 00:21:01.582
"It is what makes him sad
and what makes him want."

163
00:21:04.858 --> 00:21:07.915
"He will go on taking and taking...

164
00:21:09.125 --> 00:21:12.319
"Until one day the World will say:

165
00:21:13.092 --> 00:21:17.218
"I am no more
and I have nothing left to give."

166
00:22:03.926 --> 00:22:05.755
Come back to me...

167
00:22:10.093 --> 00:22:11.956
Come back to me.

168
00:22:40.827 --> 00:22:42.816
My son is dancing.

169
00:22:44.527 --> 00:22:46.652
Your son is happy.

170
00:23:38.995 --> 00:23:40.654
What do you want?

171
00:23:56.661 --> 00:23:58.388
Run!

172
00:24:13.928 --> 00:24:17.951
Now that you're up.
can you please kill that dog?

173
00:24:31.095 --> 00:24:33.152
The dog.

174
00:26:00.696 --> 00:26:02.287
Get up! Get up! Now!

175
00:27:17.964 --> 00:27:19.554
Go to the forest.

176
00:27:19.998 --> 00:27:21.827
Run! Do not look back.

177
00:27:47.598 --> 00:27:49.427
No! No! I am afraid!

178
00:27:49.799 --> 00:27:51.822
Look into my eyes. Look into my eyes.

179
00:27:52.165 --> 00:27:53.222
Be strong...

180
00:27:53.665 --> 00:27:54.756
I am afraid!

181
00:27:55.365 --> 00:27:56.888
Be strong.

182
00:28:55.266 --> 00:28:56.129
Tie him up!

183
00:30:14.201 --> 00:30:15.224
Father!

184
00:30:16.634 --> 00:30:18.793
The others. I have to help.

185
00:30:19.934 --> 00:30:21.661
No. don't leave us!

186
00:30:21.967 --> 00:30:24.626
I will come back. I promise.

187
00:30:24.934 --> 00:30:26.127
Don't you leave!

188
00:30:26.434 --> 00:30:27.264
I promise.

189
00:30:27.334 --> 00:30:28.231
Stay. please stay.

190
00:30:28.467 --> 00:30:29.592
Father. don't go.

191
00:31:26.169 --> 00:31:27.566
Very nice.

192
00:32:14.536 --> 00:32:15.559
Stop!

193
00:32:24.369 --> 00:32:25.665
Tie him up!

194
00:32:30.036 --> 00:32:31.433
I want him alive.

195
00:32:51.969 --> 00:32:53.230
Sorry Father.

196
00:33:12.336 --> 00:33:14.234
That's enough!

197
00:33:24.837 --> 00:33:26.598
Stand him up.

198
00:33:34.336 --> 00:33:35.962
Move away.

199
00:33:49.804 --> 00:33:51.566
My son.

200
00:34:02.438 --> 00:34:04.233
Don't be afraid.

201
00:35:02.505 --> 00:35:04.970
Almost...

202
00:35:19.872 --> 00:35:22.463
...that's your name.

203
00:35:23.472 --> 00:35:26.632
"Almost".

204
00:35:42.505 --> 00:35:44.971
Our life is over.

205
00:35:50.373 --> 00:35:51.668
Shame...

206
00:35:59.705 --> 00:36:00.932
Shame!

207
00:36:05.106 --> 00:36:07.163
Cowards!

208
00:39:40.643 --> 00:39:42.404
Let's move!

209
00:42:01.945 --> 00:42:03.308
We move out now.

210
00:42:03.711 --> 00:42:05.143
They are back.

211
00:42:08.179 --> 00:42:09.508
Get up!

212
00:42:12.312 --> 00:42:13.743
Heave!

213
00:42:20.945 --> 00:42:23.672
Cut Rock. you forgot to duck.

214
00:42:26.678 --> 00:42:27.974
Hold still.

215
00:42:37.679 --> 00:42:38.803
Can you see?

216
00:42:41.212 --> 00:42:42.143
Yes.

217
00:42:42.612 --> 00:42:44.407
Get back to your line.

218
00:43:45.780 --> 00:43:46.972
Come with us...

219
00:44:39.281 --> 00:44:40.474
Get up.

220
00:44:53.047 --> 00:44:55.309
Leave him alone. "Almost".

221
00:44:57.481 --> 00:44:59.344
I said get up.

222
00:45:27.881 --> 00:45:29.608
Up. up...

223
00:45:30.115 --> 00:45:31.671
...that's it.

224
00:45:33.815 --> 00:45:35.145
Let's go!

225
00:45:39.015 --> 00:45:41.913
This man is a good friend of yours...

226
00:46:16.782 --> 00:46:18.748
Don't worry...

227
00:46:22.315 --> 00:46:24.282
I'll take care of them.

228
00:46:27.216 --> 00:46:29.511
They are mine now.

229
00:46:36.782 --> 00:46:40.839
Gentle Ixchel. Tender mother of mercy.

230
00:46:42.682 --> 00:46:47.808
Keep them from harm. Please. Keep them.

231
00:47:23.683 --> 00:47:25.273
One more.

232
00:47:48.883 --> 00:47:50.577
Ready?

233
00:48:51.452 --> 00:48:53.008
Hold on! Hold on!

234
00:48:56.951 --> 00:48:58.508
Wait...

235
00:49:00.051 --> 00:49:01.846
...let's see what happens.

236
00:49:09.852 --> 00:49:10.749
That's it!

237
00:49:17.985 --> 00:49:19.177
Hurry!

238
00:49:20.151 --> 00:49:22.083
Pull! Be strong!

239
00:49:41.119 --> 00:49:42.948
Yes! You did it!

240
00:49:46.819 --> 00:49:48.479
Good work!

241
00:50:01.286 --> 00:50:04.013
Can you breathe...? Good.

242
00:50:33.786 --> 00:50:34.683
Wait here.

243
00:51:08.020 --> 00:51:09.680
What's become of my capture?

244
00:51:13.487 --> 00:51:14.918
Dead weight.

245
00:51:16.620 --> 00:51:18.848
He nearly took the rest with him.

246
00:51:21.120 --> 00:51:22.814
I let him go.

247
00:51:27.053 --> 00:51:28.781
You. Let him go?

248
00:51:35.854 --> 00:51:39.342
Shall we now do what you want?

249
00:51:43.687 --> 00:51:46.653
Let us try that.

250
00:52:09.887 --> 00:52:12.683
Don't let any others go.

251
00:52:19.354 --> 00:52:20.615
Let's move.

252
00:52:35.888 --> 00:52:38.013
Get up "Almost".

253
00:52:39.122 --> 00:52:42.679
We don't want to lose you just yet.

254
00:53:32.823 --> 00:53:34.812
Stand up. boy.

255
00:53:43.556 --> 00:53:46.079
You proved yourself today. my son.

256
00:53:46.789 --> 00:53:50.585
You're now worthy to stand
with the rest of us.

257
00:53:53.156 --> 00:53:55.678
Thank you Father.

258
00:54:05.722 --> 00:54:07.120
Take it...

259
00:54:07.856 --> 00:54:09.083
...it's yours.

260
00:54:13.190 --> 00:54:15.815
It has taken many lives.

261
00:54:28.190 --> 00:54:29.622
Get some rest.

262
00:54:44.123 --> 00:54:45.282
Resting brothers...

263
00:54:45.557 --> 00:54:48.921
...fathers. mothers. wives.

264
00:54:49.957 --> 00:54:54.117
You felt the cold
of this day's early morning.

265
00:54:55.057 --> 00:54:59.251
Now you cannot feel
the coldness of its night.

266
00:55:01.957 --> 00:55:03.946
She stopped screaming...

267
00:55:06.157 --> 00:55:09.123
...too long before they returned.
she had stopped screaming.

268
00:55:09.990 --> 00:55:12.649
We saw how she fought them.

269
00:55:13.690 --> 00:55:15.520
But in the final moment?

270
00:55:17.124 --> 00:55:19.022
If she let them...

271
00:55:21.690 --> 00:55:26.316
...the Goddess of the Scaffold
shows no mercy for the weakness...

272
00:55:28.357 --> 00:55:32.813
Her soul waits for yours
in the shade of the Ceiba Tree.

273
00:55:43.991 --> 00:55:45.684
I need to know.

274
00:55:47.191 --> 00:55:51.988
Before this day's end
I will leave this world.

275
00:55:53.891 --> 00:55:59.346
I will take as many
of these bastard dogs with me as I can.

276
00:56:01.691 --> 00:56:06.487
And I will gladly embrace
the torments of hell...

277
00:56:08.658 --> 00:56:12.022
...if I do not find my Sky Flower there.

278
00:56:19.058 --> 00:56:20.524
Don't rain.

279
00:57:03.826 --> 00:57:05.621
I am walking here.

280
00:57:38.393 --> 00:57:40.416
Keep away. she has the sickness.

281
00:58:05.993 --> 00:58:07.652
Get back!

282
00:59:00.494 --> 00:59:02.619
You fear me?

283
00:59:04.028 --> 00:59:06.619
So you should...

284
00:59:07.294 --> 00:59:10.692
...all you who are vile.

285
00:59:13.727 --> 00:59:17.251
Would you like to know how you will die?

286
00:59:24.295 --> 00:59:28.125
The sacred time is near...

287
00:59:30.295 --> 00:59:34.455
Beware the blackness of day.

288
00:59:37.662 --> 00:59:42.424
Beware the man who brings the jaguar.

289
00:59:45.328 --> 00:59:49.987
Behold him reborn from mud and earth...

290
00:59:51.061 --> 00:59:56.926
For the one he takes you to
will cancel the sky...

291
00:59:58.061 --> 01:00:00.926
...and scratch out the earth.

292
01:00:02.061 --> 01:00:04.357
Scratch you out.

293
01:00:05.628 --> 01:00:08.321
And end your world.

294
01:00:14.895 --> 01:00:18.020
He's with us now.

295
01:00:24.995 --> 01:00:27.825
...day will be like night.

296
01:00:28.362 --> 01:00:32.919
And the man jaguar
will lead you to your end.

297
01:01:43.830 --> 01:01:46.092
Where are they taking us?

298
01:01:50.397 --> 01:01:54.796
We tell stories of a place stone-built.

299
01:01:56.330 --> 01:01:57.852
What happens there?

300
01:01:58.797 --> 01:02:00.194
I do not know...

301
01:02:01.730 --> 01:02:05.253
...but the earth bleeds.

302
01:02:08.297 --> 01:02:10.195
We are near.

303
01:02:51.864 --> 01:02:53.455
Salvation!

304
01:02:54.064 --> 01:02:57.121
He has the laughing sickness.

305
01:02:58.131 --> 01:03:00.154
He likes you!

306
01:03:02.731 --> 01:03:03.957
Help me!

307
01:03:12.331 --> 01:03:14.160
Save me.

308
01:03:22.065 --> 01:03:23.621
Die like a man.

309
01:06:04.067 --> 01:06:05.158
Welcome back.

310
01:06:06.301 --> 01:06:07.766
Have you been successful?

311
01:06:08.367 --> 01:06:09.458
Ask my son.

312
01:06:11.401 --> 01:06:12.765
How many captives?

313
01:06:13.000 --> 01:06:13.966
Deal with my son.

314
01:06:16.067 --> 01:06:17.124
A fair price.

315
01:06:18.568 --> 01:06:20.329
As always. trust me.

316
01:06:21.167 --> 01:06:21.826
Good.

317
01:06:39.668 --> 01:06:42.361
How much will you give me?

318
01:07:44.036 --> 01:07:45.934
Who will buy this woman?

319
01:07:47.002 --> 01:07:48.365
No... she's too old.

320
01:07:49.702 --> 01:07:51.497
She can be useful.

321
01:07:52.002 --> 01:07:53.695
She can cook... clean...

322
01:07:55.236 --> 01:07:57.293
Useless old woman!

323
01:08:00.969 --> 01:08:02.492
No sale.

324
01:08:08.236 --> 01:08:09.600
Go!

325
01:08:10.702 --> 01:08:11.963
Go on.

326
01:13:12.660 --> 01:13:16.952
These are the days of our great lament.

327
01:13:21.411 --> 01:13:23.328
The land thirsts.

328
01:13:25.744 --> 01:13:30.161
A great plague infests our crops.

329
01:13:32.994 --> 01:13:37.036
The scourge of sickness
afflicts us at whim.

330
01:13:43.036 --> 01:13:46.661
They say this strife has made us weak.

331
01:13:48.870 --> 01:13:50.703
That we have become empty.

332
01:13:53.536 --> 01:13:55.786
They say that we rot.

333
01:14:07.494 --> 01:14:10.369
Great people of the banner of the sun...

334
01:14:11.203 --> 01:14:12.661
I say...

335
01:14:13.870 --> 01:14:15.661
...we are strong.

336
01:14:20.162 --> 01:14:22.203
We are a people of destiny.

337
01:14:27.037 --> 01:14:30.287
Destined to be the masters of time.

338
01:14:34.370 --> 01:14:37.621
Destined to be nearest to the gods.

339
01:14:53.537 --> 01:14:56.662
Mighty Kukulkan!

340
01:14:58.329 --> 01:15:02.829
Whose fury could scorch
this earth to oblivion...

341
01:15:05.495 --> 01:15:07.787
Let us appease you with this sacrifice.

342
01:15:08.370 --> 01:15:10.203
To exalt you in your glory.

343
01:15:11.038 --> 01:15:13.662
To make our people prosper.

344
01:15:14.746 --> 01:15:17.495
To prepare for your return.

345
01:15:20.537 --> 01:15:23.330
Warrior. unafraid and willing!

346
01:15:23.871 --> 01:15:26.205
With your blood you renew the world!

347
01:15:26.746 --> 01:15:28.537
From age to age.

348
01:15:29.996 --> 01:15:31.621
Thanks be to you.

349
01:15:46.371 --> 01:15:48.496
The heart of god!

350
01:18:32.041 --> 01:18:34.333
Come back to me.

351
01:18:43.249 --> 01:18:45.124
Brother...

352
01:18:47.041 --> 01:18:48.832
Journey well...

353
01:18:50.999 --> 01:18:51.874
No.

354
01:18:53.375 --> 01:18:54.500
I can't go.

355
01:18:56.041 --> 01:18:57.625
Not now...

356
01:21:17.210 --> 01:21:22.043
People of the banner
of the sun do not fear.

357
01:21:23.001 --> 01:21:24.835
Rejoice!

358
01:21:26.085 --> 01:21:29.126
Kukulkan has drunk his fill of blood.

359
01:21:29.502 --> 01:21:32.293
We have sated his thirst.

360
01:21:33.418 --> 01:21:35.127
Great god.

361
01:21:36.086 --> 01:21:38.335
Show us that you are pleased.

362
01:21:38.585 --> 01:21:42.169
Let your light return upon us.

363
01:22:47.503 --> 01:22:49.545
What of these captives?

364
01:22:54.254 --> 01:22:56.170
Dispose of them.

365
01:23:30.546 --> 01:23:32.712
I need a finisher.

366
01:23:37.754 --> 01:23:39.046
You.

367
01:23:45.171 --> 01:23:46.713
Release them.

368
01:23:55.004 --> 01:23:56.629
You watch.

369
01:24:17.505 --> 01:24:18.547
I'm ready!

370
01:24:23.547 --> 01:24:26.547
There's your jungle beyond the corn.

371
01:24:29.505 --> 01:24:30.880
Go to it.

372
01:24:31.714 --> 01:24:33.130
You're free...

373
01:24:35.005 --> 01:24:36.338
...now run.

374
01:24:39.714 --> 01:24:41.006
I said run.

375
01:24:45.422 --> 01:24:46.672
Run!

376
01:26:00.257 --> 01:26:01.339
Not bad.

377
01:26:19.507 --> 01:26:20.840
Your turn.

378
01:26:28.674 --> 01:26:30.173
Run.

379
01:27:46.008 --> 01:27:47.466
Run!

380
01:29:01.885 --> 01:29:03.468
Sleep.

381
01:29:04.426 --> 01:29:06.676
Sleep. sleep now my son.

382
01:29:07.718 --> 01:29:10.051
The pain will be no more.

383
01:29:12.051 --> 01:29:13.302
Sleep.

384
01:35:03.057 --> 01:35:05.182
He didn't come this way.

385
01:35:18.432 --> 01:35:20.391
He's in the trees.

386
01:35:22.182 --> 01:35:23.391
Spread out.

387
01:35:24.265 --> 01:35:25.808
Keep your eyes up.

388
01:35:48.183 --> 01:35:49.225
Quiet.

389
01:36:00.849 --> 01:36:02.016
He's coming right at us.

390
01:36:18.725 --> 01:36:19.392
There!

391
01:38:17.519 --> 01:38:20.227
He would have wanted me to have it.

392
01:38:22.394 --> 01:38:25.352
The omen is bad...

393
01:38:27.269 --> 01:38:30.352
Mighty Ek Chuah we beg you...

394
01:38:31.602 --> 01:38:35.853
Forgive us for this trespass
against your son the Jaguar.

395
01:38:37.853 --> 01:38:40.310
The omen is bad...

396
01:38:42.061 --> 01:38:44.061
Lift yourself up Drunkards Four...

397
01:38:44.894 --> 01:38:47.894
...the omen was foretold...

398
01:38:50.270 --> 01:38:53.477
...and now we have a fear more grave...

399
01:38:54.435 --> 01:38:57.853
...today I saw the day
become like night...

400
01:39:04.395 --> 01:39:08.019
I saw a man run with the Jaguar...

401
01:39:11.894 --> 01:39:16.019
...we must not let this man
make feet from us.

402
01:39:16.727 --> 01:39:17.894
Enough.

403
01:39:21.687 --> 01:39:23.520
Your words mean nothing.

404
01:39:24.894 --> 01:39:27.145
He runs because he is afraid.

405
01:39:28.520 --> 01:39:32.145
When I catch him.
I will peel his skin...

406
01:39:35.186 --> 01:39:37.895
...and have him watch me wear it.

407
01:39:45.603 --> 01:39:46.854
We leave now.

408
01:41:54.355 --> 01:41:55.522
Stay back.

409
01:43:06.398 --> 01:43:07.523
Here!

410
01:43:32.065 --> 01:43:34.190
The omen was bad...

411
01:43:37.899 --> 01:43:39.024
He's fucked.

412
01:43:42.357 --> 01:43:43.733
Help... please...

413
01:43:44.566 --> 01:43:45.858
Hanging Moss...

414
01:43:47.524 --> 01:43:49.149
See him out.

415
01:44:09.566 --> 01:44:13.233
Open your veins. It's quicker.

416
01:44:25.941 --> 01:44:28.025
Travel well.

417
01:47:33.694 --> 01:47:36.403
So much for your prophecies.

418
01:47:42.278 --> 01:47:43.528
It's not over!

419
01:48:09.528 --> 01:48:11.153
I am Jaguar Paw...

420
01:48:11.862 --> 01:48:13.403
Son of Flint Sky...

421
01:48:14.862 --> 01:48:18.195
My father hunted
this forest before me...

422
01:48:19.946 --> 01:48:21.904
My name is Jaguar Paw.

423
01:48:22.737 --> 01:48:24.362
I am a hunter.

424
01:48:25.946 --> 01:48:28.196
This is my forest.

425
01:48:29.403 --> 01:48:33.904
And my sons will hunt it
with their sons after I am gone...

426
01:48:36.779 --> 01:48:38.029
Come on!

427
01:48:40.695 --> 01:48:42.363
We are going over.

428
01:48:42.946 --> 01:48:45.695
We climb down around.

429
01:48:46.946 --> 01:48:49.029
We cannot let him get away.

430
01:48:49.737 --> 01:48:50.862
We cannot afford...

431
01:49:11.071 --> 01:49:13.196
We all jump.

432
01:52:10.074 --> 01:52:11.700
I am Jaguar Paw.

433
01:52:13.574 --> 01:52:15.366
This is my forest.

434
01:52:17.449 --> 01:52:20.157
And I am not afraid.

435
01:54:27.451 --> 01:54:30.034
You go. I'll wait here.

436
01:59:59.248 --> 02:00:01.041
Almost...

437
02:00:27.874 --> 02:00:30.540
Resting fathers. fly me your strength.

438
02:00:57.583 --> 02:00:59.333
Get up here.

439
02:01:14.208 --> 02:01:15.750
Go back!

440
02:01:45.125 --> 02:01:45.833
Quick!

441
02:01:46.417 --> 02:01:47.417
Hurry up!

442
02:08:13.881 --> 02:08:15.715
What are they?

443
02:08:17.424 --> 02:08:19.215
They bring men.

444
02:08:23.882 --> 02:08:25.757
Should we go to them?

445
02:08:34.090 --> 02:08:35.882
We should go to the forest.

446
02:08:42.757 --> 02:08:44.674
To seek a new beginning.

447
02:08:49.799 --> 02:08:51.216
Come Turtles Run...

